---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-kanpur.html" headerVariant="guide">

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Local Solar Guide · Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh</div>
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">Rooftop Solar in Kanpur</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Kanpur homeowners are reducing DVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies. This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started in Kanpur.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Check My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">DVVNL</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Dakshinanchal / UPPCL</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Kanpur</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Strong Solar Irradiance</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Kanpur receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day on average. As one of UP's major industrial and residential cities, rooftop solar is well-suited for Kanpur homes and offers strong financial returns.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">High Summer Bills & Solar Peak</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Kanpur summers are among the hottest in UP, driving significant cooling loads and high DVVNL bills. Solar panels generate maximum output through exactly these months — directly offsetting your highest-cost electricity.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising DVVNL Tariffs</h3><p class="text-slate-600">DVVNL domestic electricity tariffs have increased steadily. Rooftop solar locks in self-generated power at zero marginal cost, shielding your household from further tariff hikes over the system's lifetime.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Eligibility</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Kanpur homeowners with a DVVNL electricity connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy. DVVNL maintains an empanelled installer list for Kanpur on pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">DVVNL Net Metering in Kanpur</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Kanpur homeowners under DVVNL.</p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via DVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be empanelled with DVVNL under the PM Surya Ghar scheme. Verify on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to DVVNL</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to DVVNL with technical system details. Most empanelled installers handle this on your behalf.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">DVVNL Technical Inspection</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A DVVNL engineer inspects the installation to verify grid safety compliance. Typically two to four weeks in Kanpur depending on DVVNL workload.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing DVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter measuring both electricity imported and exported to the grid. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once DVVNL commissions your system, surplus solar exported to the grid earns credits on your monthly DVVNL electricity bill going forward.</p></div></div>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a> for a full explanation of how bill credits work.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Kanpur</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly DVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly DVVNL Bill</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr><td class="p-4">₹1,000 – ₹2,500</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK</td></tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50"><td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td><td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹7,000+</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="10kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">10kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">800–1,000 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Large bungalows, kothi</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a> for the full methodology.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Kanpur</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Kanpur homeowners with a DVVNL connection can apply for the PM Surya Ghar central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div></div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as a Kanpur Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your DVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select a DVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's list</li>
<li>3. Get system installed, net metering connected, DVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited directly to your bank account — typically weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Verify current rates at pmsuryaghar.gov.in before making financial decisions.</p>
</div>
<div class="mt-4"><a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →</a></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Kanpur Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">We help homeowners across Kanpur connect with DVVNL-empanelled installers in their area.</p>
<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{["Civil Lines", "Kidwai Nagar", "Swaroop Nagar", "Kalyanpur", "Govind Nagar", "Armapur", "Rawatpur", "Juhi", "Kakadeo", "Panki", "Fazalganj", "Naubasta", "GT Road", "Benajhabar", "Sarsaul", "Barra"].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Kanpur Solar</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Kanpur?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Kanpur falls under <strong>DVVNL (Dakshinanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary covering southern UP. All net metering applications, bi-directional meter installations, and solar scheme empanelment for Kanpur homeowners are processed through DVVNL.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with DVVNL in Kanpur?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by a DVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to DVVNL. DVVNL inspects the system and installs a bi-directional meter. The process typically takes two to six weeks in Kanpur.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Kanpur?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Kanpur homeowners with a DVVNL connection are eligible. Use a DVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current subsidy amounts before applying.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Kanpur homes?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For typical Kanpur homes with monthly DVVNL bills of ₹2,000–₹5,000, a 2kW to 3kW system covers a significant share of electricity needs. Larger homes or those with heavy AC use through summer may benefit from 3kW to 5kW.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Kanpur?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After PM Surya Ghar subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Compare quotes from at least two DVVNL-empanelled installers before deciding.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is Kanpur a good location for solar?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Kanpur receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours daily. Intense summers — when DVVNL bills peak — coincide with maximum solar generation, making solar financially effective for most Kanpur homeowners.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
<p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Also serving homeowners in <a href="rooftop-solar-lucknow.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Lucknow</a>, <a href="rooftop-solar-prayagraj.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Prayagraj</a> and <a href="rooftop-solar-varanasi.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Varanasi</a>. <a href="cities.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">View all city guides →</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Helpful Guides for Kanpur Homeowners</h2>
<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Subsidies</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">PM Surya Ghar Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Billing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Net Metering Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/how-to-choose-solar-installer.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Installers</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">How to Choose an Installer</div></a>
<a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Sizing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Solar System Sizing Guide</div></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-[2rem] p-10">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">See How Much You Can Save in Kanpur</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-8">Get a personalised solar savings estimate based on your DVVNL bill — in under 60 seconds.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Calculate My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
